  "technicalDetails": "<h1>Features:</h1><p><br /></p><h2>1.Hit Reactions:</h2><ol><li>Hit Material Glow: the actor&#39;s material glow bright</li><li>Hit Squeeze Squash: the actor&#39;s mesh performs squeeze squash</li><li>Hit Damage Text: pool user widget that shows damage amount with number</li><li>Hit Update Healthbar: add a health bar and update it</li><li>Hit Knocked Back: actor gets knocked back from the damage causer&#39;s direction</li><li>Hit Particle Effect: spawn a particle emitter</li><li>Hit Montage: skeletal mesh play montage </li></ol><p><br /></p><h2>2.Death Reactions:</h2><ol><li>Death Material Dissolve: mesh material dissolves away</li><li>Death Particle Effect: spawn a particle emitter</li><li>Death Anim: choose either play montage mode or ragdoll mode.</li><li>Death Drop Loot: spawn actors from class list </li><li>Death Auto Destroy: destroy the actor after a delay</li></ol><p><br /></p><h2>3.Damage Dealing Mechanics</h2><p>which i think is the unreal engine best practice.</p><p><br /></p><p>---------------------------------------------------------------------</p><p><br /></p><h2>Documentation:</h2><p>https://drive.google.com/file/d/1Zqgm5cSvNUvb5oXmnJUrustZjylfUuub/view?usp&#61;drive_link</p><p><br /></p><h2>Demonstration Video:</h2><p>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v&#61;RroOBjtQ1XI</p><p><br /></p><h2>Email:</h2><p>leroy-mackerl4&#64;hotmail.com</p><p><br /></p><p>---------------------------------------------------------------------</p><p><br /></p><p>Number of Blueprints: 33, including demo content.</p><p>Input: Mouse ( for demo room )</p><p>Supported Development Platforms:</p><p>Windows: (Yes)</p><p>Mac: (Not Tested)</p><p>Network Replicated: No</p>",
